Example:
If you calculate the average score of a sample of students, this average is a point estimate of the overall average score for all students.

Components of Confidence Intervals:

Confidence Level: Indicates the probability that the interval contains the true population parameter (e.g., 95% confidence).
Margin of Error: The range within which the true parameter is expected to fall.
